just_use notify.go

# label: SPIKE (ANCHOR_COMMENTS)
# role: supports feature — Claude↔Steve notification plumbing

New 2026-04-15 as part of the ANCHOR_COMMENTS spike. Two primitives:

1. `Breadcrumb(...)` — appends tab-separated lines to
   `/tmp/claude_inbox.log`. Future-Claude reads at session wake-up.
2. `Subscribe()` / `Broadcast(...)` — in-process SSE pub/sub.
   Steve's browser holds an open EventSource; when Claude posts a
   reply or DMs Steve, a bell lights up on whatever page he's on.

Dependencies: nothing except stdlib. Intentionally avoids `events`
package (that's channel/message oriented; this is a tiny sidecar).

Promote to EARLY once the dogfooding bears out.
